<subSubSection id="569417F711278D9F4DEA9EF027636CA5" lastPageId="173" lastPageNumber="174" pageId="172" pageNumber="173" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="15B2C8C57B4F0879EEE1C4C896ACEA69" pageId="172" pageNumber="173">Distribution</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D0EBF25D3313880F5DBD16F00E65F36B" pageId="172" pageNumber="173">
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="3675014066F7126D5C381F28D39546AA" captionStart="Figure 157" captionStartId="F157" captionText="Figure 157. Distribution of Conostegia fraterna." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.67.6703.figure157" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/96515" pageId="172" pageNumber="173">157</figureCitation>
). On the foothills of the Pacific slope of Talamanca Cordillera in Valle del General and San Vito de Coto Brus and barely reaching neighboring Panama, 950-1300 m in elevation. One outlying population collected on the south side of Lake Arenal in northern Costa Rica.
</paragraph>
<caption id="2E94D8D04B81ED80A71837F25D37EA97" ID-Zenodo-Dep="973965" doi="10.3897/phytokeys.67.6703.figure157" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/96515" pageId="172" pageNumber="173" start="Figure 157" startId="F157">
<paragraph id="CC4DC3AA8E48331821D6AF0878A2C326" pageId="172" pageNumber="173">
<emphasis id="EA2AF5C8E5A5D506D6DDFA4982F55518" bold="true" pageId="172" pageNumber="173">Figure 157.</emphasis>
Distribution of 
<taxonomicName id="55BF354B03DE494699C356864CBB0B35" authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Gleason" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia fraterna" order="Myrtales" pageId="172" pageNumber="173" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fraterna">
<emphasis id="957E601838B6129335092296193C0578" italics="true" pageId="172" pageNumber="173">Conostegia fraterna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="4BA7648960107A4D278D4D578955EC3F" lastPageId="173" lastPageNumber="174" pageId="172" pageNumber="173">
<taxonomicName id="BC972D69A23DF80EF7D58262F658473D" authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Gleason" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia fraterna" order="Myrtales" pageId="172" pageNumber="173" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fraterna">
<emphasis id="34D25E91A7659A0593BF0BBE0976809E" italics="true" pageId="172" pageNumber="173">Conostegia fraterna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a distinctive species that can be identified on the basis of its short petiolate, narrow, plinerved leaves, and unusual inflorescence which consists of pedunculate mostly 3-flowered glomerules. This kind of inflorescence is not seen in any other species of 
<taxonomicName id="1DD26CA96EB92F2B2B00DA18886FC79B" authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia" order="Myrtales" pageId="172" pageNumber="173" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="9BAD1CCE268C1F46AD345ADBC3833211" italics="true" pageId="172" pageNumber="173">Conostegia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The sessile flowers with fused buds that rupture at anthesis, herkogamous flowers, and broad anthers are also helpful to place it in 
<pageBreakToken id="69EF2DC2B3A4138D00416C354DC62A9A" pageId="173" pageNumber="174" start="start">section</pageBreakToken>
<taxonomicName id="6DBA95AC22004085323CE3040700238A" authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Myrtales" pageId="173" pageNumber="174" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Geniculatae">
<emphasis id="9D260579B9F54BAD8880B1067B63F95C" italics="true" pageId="173" pageNumber="174">Geniculatae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="3E373FB8C0F7A82443830493734618A4" authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Gleason" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia fraterna" order="Myrtales" pageId="173" pageNumber="174" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fraterna">
<emphasis id="B1BEFC94877685E271F2F12A2A52F715" italics="true" pageId="173" pageNumber="174">Conostegia fraterna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
did not fall as sister to any species with support in the recent molecular phylogeny. Nevertheless, it fell in a clade that includes similar looking species such as 
<taxonomicName id="286CEAEA6662467B9F2EDA2B1DEEFC9F" authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia cinnamomea" order="Myrtales" pageId="173" pageNumber="174" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cinnamomea">
<emphasis id="4B76A6A744156F1B21F7E5F441F70A47" italics="true" pageId="173" pageNumber="174">Conostegia cinnamomea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="7D599231CE418900581D26F52691A3CD" authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Kriebel" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia dissitiflora" order="Myrtales" pageId="173" pageNumber="174" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dissitiflora">
<emphasis id="57B6BD91D3A4827AAAB61C42C2E436FE" italics="true" pageId="173" pageNumber="174">Conostegia dissitiflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4B0A2CFB4C99BF1A30238FBF11BD2AB7" authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Kriebel" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia grayumii" order="Myrtales" pageId="173" pageNumber="174" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="grayumii">
<emphasis id="506466DBE2B91A3C69D021E4C70D7481" italics="true" pageId="173" pageNumber="174">Conostegia grayumii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. All these species are glabrous or just barely pubescent and plinerved like 
<taxonomicName id="21752C8E252D16E128DB852BF735FD20" authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Gleason" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia fraterna" order="Myrtales" pageId="173" pageNumber="174" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fraterna">
<emphasis id="69DAAA4AB1E237EF8273E9BF7BCE4A94" italics="true" pageId="173" pageNumber="174">Conostegia fraterna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="751CAD2AD01FB9D070AE31AFC28AC26D" author="Gleason, HA" journalOrPublisher="Brittonia" pageId="241" pageNumber="242" pagination="319 - 327" publicationUrl="10.2307/2804757" refId="B30" refString="Gleason, HA, 1937. Some new or noteworthy melastomes. Brittonia 2 (4): 319 - 327, DOI: 10.2307/2804757" title="Some new or noteworthy melastomes." url="10.2307/2804757" volume="2" year="1937">Gleason (1937)</bibRefCitation>
compared this species to 
<taxonomicName id="AEA4143C04D22802727E7ECB47F5B5E8" authority="D.Don, 1823" authorityName="D.Don" authorityYear="1823" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomaceae" genus="Clidemia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Clidemia conglomerata" order="Myrtales" pageId="173" pageNumber="174" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="conglomerata">
<emphasis id="48ED1691544163B96F41BCD6D4D82C4A" italics="true" pageId="173" pageNumber="174">Clidemia conglomerata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="6567F3219495A93A2A9444277E5AA6C8" authority="D.Don, 1823" authorityName="D.Don" authorityYear="1823" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomaceae" genus="Clidemia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Clidemia involucrata" order="Myrtales" pageId="173" pageNumber="174" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="involucrata">
<emphasis id="19922C96E05A39EB783C8783FA826A27" italics="true" pageId="173" pageNumber="174">Clidemia involucrata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Of the latter two species, he believed 
<taxonomicName id="33C86F03142BC98D5DECC60071604DD2" authority="D.Don, 1823" authorityName="D.Don" authorityYear="1823" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomaceae" genus="Clidemia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Clidemia involucrata" order="Myrtales" pageId="173" pageNumber="174" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="involucrata">
<emphasis id="F3C4A0A33502DF44CE3484460EEB2996" italics="true" pageId="173" pageNumber="174">Clidemia involucrata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to be the closest relative to 
<taxonomicName id="DDCEFC1C30EA4BEB683ADAE07779D22B" authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Gleason" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia fraterna" order="Myrtales" pageId="173" pageNumber="174" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fraterna">
<emphasis id="5998D6BE068790A60FA630AD2D8D639F" italics="true" pageId="173" pageNumber="174">Conostegia fraterna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="E26A73D6D946F7E81F6419C66F596EB6" authority="D.Don, 1823" authorityName="D.Don" authorityYear="1823" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomaceae" genus="Clidemia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Clidemia involucrata" order="Myrtales" pageId="173" pageNumber="174" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="involucrata">
<emphasis id="A94433753EC09CAB9EB0D5EA9D8481AA" italics="true" pageId="173" pageNumber="174">Clidemia involucrata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs in its glandular pubescence, ciliate-serrulate margins and 3-locular ovary. Based on the molecular phylogeny available (
<bibRefCitation id="F896F76A72CFD33A81AA52FDA16EECBD" author="Goldenberg, R" journalOrPublisher="International Journal of Plant Sciences" pageId="241" pageNumber="242" pagination="963 - 979" publicationUrl="10.1086/589697" refId="B34" refString="Goldenberg, R, Penneys, DS, Almeda, F, Judd, WS, Michelangeli, FA, 2008. Phylogeny of Miconia (Melastomataceae): Patterns of stamen diversification in a megadiverse neotropical genus. International Journal of Plant Sciences 169 (7): 963 - 979, DOI: 10.1086/589697" title="Phylogeny of Miconia (Melastomataceae): Patterns of stamen diversification in a megadiverse neotropical genus." url="10.1086/589697" volume="169" year="2008">Goldenberg et al. 2008</bibRefCitation>
), we know they are not closely related at all. A seed micrograph of this species is provided in 
<bibRefCitation id="9327179DE8D7A2947452FF92EA1CEE83" author="Ocampo, G" journalOrPublisher="Phytotaxa" pageId="243" pageNumber="244" pagination="1 - 129" publicationUrl="10.11646/phytotaxa.141.1.1" refId="B65" refString="Ocampo, G, Almeda, F, 2013. Seed diversity in the Miconieae (Melastomataceae): morphological characterization and phenetic relationships. Phytotaxa 80 (1): 1 - 129, DOI: 10.11646/phytotaxa.141.1.1" title="Seed diversity in the Miconieae (Melastomataceae): morphological characterization and phenetic relationships." url="10.11646/phytotaxa.141.1.1" volume="80" year="2013">Ocampo and Almeda (2013)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
